	Ryan waves his hand dismissively.
	Ryan: So what? I write notes to myself all the time.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S5/The_Protagonist_pulls_out_the_second_piece.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	The Protagonist pulls out the second piece of paper - the threatening note.
	Conrad: This note was left in Ria's locker three days ago.
	Conrad: "I know what you did with last year's fund. Resign or I'll expose you."
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S5/Ryans_face_goes_pale.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	audio music "res://assets/audio/bg/chill.mp3" [loop="true"]
	Ryan's face goes pale.
	Conrad: The handwriting is identical, Ryan. Same loops on the 'e'. Same sharp angles on the 'k'.
	Conrad: You wrote this threat. You knew about Ria's mistake because you've been watching the council.
	Conrad: Waiting for your chance.
	Ryan: That... that doesn't prove anything.
	Conrad: The printer logs show you stopped printing for over an hour yesterday evening.
	Conrad: During that exact time, Ms. Santos left the faculty room for coffee.
	Conrad: You saw her leave. You took the key from her unlocked drawer. You opened the council room.
	Conrad: And you took the money.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S5/Ryan_stands_frozen.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	join Ryan (animated_sad) right
	Ryan stands frozen, his eyes darting around the room.
	Ryan: I...
	Conrad: Where's the money, Ryan?
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S5/Ryans_shoulders_slump.mp3" volume="0.0"]
Ryan's shoulders slump. The defiance drains from his face.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S5/His_voice_comes_out_quiet_defeated.mp3" volume="0.0"]
His voice comes out quiet, defeated.
Ryan: Behind the equipment racks. In a gym bag.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S5/Mark_moves_past_Ryan.mp3" volume="0.0"]
Mark moves past Ryan and searches behind the dusty equipment.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S5/Mark_pulls_out_a_faded.mp3" volume="0.0"]
Mark pulls out a faded blue gym bag and unzips it.
Mark: Twenty thousand pesos. It's all here.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S5/Desperation_floods_Ryans_voice.mp3" volume="0.0"]
audio music "res://assets/audio/bg/chill.mp3" [loop="true"]
Desperation floods Ryan's voice.
join Ryan (animated_angry) right
Ryan: I wasn't stealing it! I was going to return it!
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Celestine: Then why take it at all?
	Ryan: I was going to "discover" it in a few days. Show everyone how easy it was to take.
	Ryan: The council is careless! Ria left the box unlocked before. Ms. Santos forgets her drawer constantly.
	Ryan: Someone had to prove that we need better systems!
	Celestine: By framing Ria? By making her cry? By letting everyone call her a thief?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S5/Ryan_flinches_at_the_protagonists_words.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ryan flinches at Celestine's words.
	join Ryan (animated_sad) right
	Ryan: I... I didn't think about it that way. I just wanted them to listen to me.
	Ryan: Nobody ever listens. They just smile and vote no. Over and over.
	Ryan: I thought if something bad happened, they'd finally pay attention.
	Celestine: There are better ways to be heard, Ryan.
	Celestine: You could have talked to teachers. Gone to the principal. Organized students who agreed with you.
	Celestine: Instead, you chose to hurt someone innocent. Someone who was already scared and alone.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S5/Ryans_voice_breaks.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ryan's voice breaks.
	join Ryan (animated_cry) right
	Ryan: I know. I know that now.
	Ryan: When I saw Ria crying this morning... I almost told the truth right there.
	Ryan: But I was too scared. Too proud.
	Celestine: This wasn't leadership. This was manipulation.
	Celestine: Good intentions don't excuse harmful actions.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 2/C2S5/Ryan_looks_at_the_floor.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	Ryan looks at the floor, unable to meet the protagonist's eyes.
	Ryan: What happens now?
	Celestine: That's not for us to decide. But the truth will come out.
	Celestine: What you do next... that's up to you.
	leave Celestine
	leave Mark
	leave Ryan
	jump c2s6/
